A vintage 1960s illustration style depicting a designer's drafting table from above, scattered with architectural blueprints and sketches of furniture, but instead of technical drawings, the papers show whimsical, unexpected inventions—a chair with wings, a telephone shaped like a seashell, a lamp that curves like a dancing figure. A single hand holding a compass hovers over the designs, about to draw something entirely new that isn't on any reference sheet. Warm amber and teal color palette with subtle paper texture and halftone dots typical of mid-century print advertisements. The mood suggests creative intuition transcending conventional requests.
